Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: it's not easy to use from the new TreasureChest gui wallet, because of  Access-Control-Allow-Origin

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: it lacks that header

Author: CHMEX#0686
Content: can you try again

Author: CHMEX#0686
Content: header("Content-type: application/json; charset=utf-8");

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: @CHMEX  ` Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` would allow any other website or nodeJS desktop app to hit the api

Author: CHMEX#0686
Content: I see let me read about that :S

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: i will try again with your change, but i don't think it will work. it's CORS/same-origin policy stuff

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: if you allow logged in users on the same domain, the header above is maybe not good

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: if you don't allow logged in users on that domain, it's relatively safe

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: i spent way too much of my life protecting elderly webapps from CSRF-attacks

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: also, you can enable that header *just* on that single read-only URL, not the whole app

Author: CHMEX#0686
Content: So I added Access-Control-Allow-Origin: * to the header

Content: i see it now

Content: let's see if that makes TreasureChest happy
